{"tid":1007491,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"澳洲悉尼正式廢除「中國新年」，稱要照顧各國人的感受","createTime":"2019-02-03T19:49:45.000Z","updateTime":"2019-02-04T02:53:09.000Z","uid":47714,"like":44,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":9,"replies":[{"pid":"7d86e7d89b06a3cae2fdba9f0be3c09e56a9b2ed","tid":1007491,"uid":47714,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-02-03T19:49:45.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"http://hkjam.com/?p=12754\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2Fhkjam.com%2F%3Fp%3D12754&d=GmsUkepvXW4IpX0DHJvToClkmYPKinjppKJkD7WQ61o%3D&h=c90d1cfe\" target=\"_blank\">http://hkjam.com/?p=12754</a><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://i1.wp.com/hkjam.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/sketch-1549091202380.png?resize=1024%2C576\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi1.wp.com%2Fhkjam.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F02%2Fsketch-1549091202380.png%3Fresize%3D1024%252C576&h=8b3909cd&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n澳洲悉尼一向有慶祝中國新年的做法，更成為了該城市一年一度的盛事，多項大型活動都會在農曆一月期間舉行，可是隨著中、澳兩國關係轉變，這項傳統或會有所不同。<br />\n<br />\n悉尼市政府宣佈，將廢除「中國新年」（Chinese New Year）這節日名稱，並會將之更名為「農曆新年」（Lunar New Year）。發言人指除中國人以外，日本和韓國等亞洲人都會慶祝農曆新年，改名是顧及了各國人的感受。<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theaustralian.com.au%2Fnews%2Fnation%2Flunar-new-year-sydney-renames-chinese-new-year-festival%2Fnews-story%2F4c834b90c111da6caacf121ce7fc6dc8\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fl.facebook.com%2Fl.php%3Fu%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.theaustralian.com.au%252Fnews%252Fnation%252Flunar-new-year-sydney-renames-chinese-new-year-festival%252Fnews-story%252F4c834b90c111da6caacf121ce7fc6dc8&d=GmsUkepvXW4IpX0DHJvToClkmYPKinjppKJkD7WQ61o%3D&h=f43aef2f\" target=\"_blank\">https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theaustralian.com.au%2Fnews%2Fnation%2Flunar-new-year-sydney-renames-chinese-new-year-festival%2Fnews-story%2F4c834b90c111da6caacf121ce7fc6dc8</a><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/D1JCQCP.png\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FD1JCQCP.png&h=dbc8f18b&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/nation/lunar-new-year-sydney-renames-chinese-new-year-festival/news-story/4c834b90c111da6caacf121ce7fc6dc8\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theaustralian.com.au%2Fnews%2Fnation%2Flunar-new-year-sydney-renames-chinese-new-year-festival%2Fnews-story%2F4c834b90c111da6caacf121ce7fc6dc8&d=GmsUkepvXW4IpX0DHJvToClkmYPKinjppKJkD7WQ61o%3D&h=04d27987\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/nation/lunar-new-year-sydney-renames-chinese-new-year-festival/news-story/4c834b90c111da6caacf121ce7fc6dc8</a><br />\n<br />\nLunar New Year: Sydney renames Chinese New Year festival<br />\n<br />\nSydney has officially rebranded its annual celebration of Chinese New Year to the Lunar New Year Festival, ending years of controversy surrounding the name of the most significant cultural event celebrated by Chinese, Vietnamese, Korean and other Asian communities in Australia.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;The Sydney Lunar Festival embraces all communities and cultures, whether or not they use the lunar calendar, and creates new opportunities for the event&rsquo;s further development,&rdquo; the spokesperson told The Australian.<br />\n<br />\nThe naming change came after Ryde and Georges River Councils (which cover areas such as Hurstville and Kogarah) adopted a more neutral Lunar New Year, following public calls from non-Chinese communities."},{"pid":"d22fa869ce8f8ffa77aa352f097f6dc81d548902","tid":1007491,"uid":7741,"like":4,"dislike":0,"score":4,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-02-03T19:54:06.000Z","msg":"正解<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2lny/kill.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2lny/kill.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2lny/kill.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2lny/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"add5bc27a05c972b2f1